// AUTO-GENERATED by scripts/50_export_dashboard_data.py — do not edit by hand.
// Named loan-modification events over the most recent quarters. Each row is
// one loan that saw a modification flip in a given quarter, with the type(s)
// and the before -> after values that triggered it. Modification flags come
// from loan_history (scripts/41_decode_position_flags.py):
//
//   pik_flip          cash-pay -> PIK this quarter
//   maturity_extended maturity_date jumped > 180 days FORWARD vs prior qtr
//   par_haircut       par dropped > 15% AND corroborated by a 2nd holder BDC
//                     (cross-BDC consensus, filters one-BDC partial sales)
//   spread_cut        cash coupon dropped > 50 bps vs prior qtr
//
// A loan can carry more than one type in a quarter (e.g. extend + PIK = a
// classic distressed amend-and-extend). before/after fields are null when
// not applicable to that row's types. MFIC and other issuers that label
// positions generically ("First Lien Secured Debt - Revolver") will show
// that label as the borrower — the modification is real, the name is coarse.

